"https://988.ca" - Suicide Crisis Helpline hub. (has direct buttons to call or text)
"https://mha.nshealth.ca/en" - Nova Scotia Mental Health Hub. Direct phone links for 911, 211 (helpline), kids help phone, mental health call, and online appointment booking, and other tools
"https://good2talk.ca/novascotia/" - Good2talk hub, with direct phone links and text
"https://www.irsss.ca/irsss-services" - Residential School survivors support hub page, with direct links to support request forms, and direct phone links.
"https://breakthesilencens.ca/find-help/where-to-get-help/" - Sexual Violence help page, has an "immediate call" link and a map for where to go
"https://translifeline.org/hotline/" - Trans help hotline, direct phone links on page for immediate action
"https://connect.nscc.ca/student/campuses/default.aspx" - NSCC non-emergency security team, page has the locations of all campuses immediately, just click on the campus and have phone numbers and emails to security contacts.
"https://togetherall.com/en-ca/" - Online community support group under the Healthy minds umbrella. Page has link button to the account creation for the site.
"https://togetherall.com/en-ca/in-crisis/: - The togetherall crisis page, direct links to a health link, mental health helpline, addiction helpline, 211 (Connects callers to community, social and government services information. Available 24/7),
and additional supports
"https://www.tranquility.app/novascotia" - online cognitive behavioural therapy program that includes online modules, interactive tools and 1-on-1 virtual coaching through text messaging and/or weekly video and phone sessions. Brings the user 
up to the home page, must create an account and sign-in in order to use the tools and services
"https://bethere.org/Home" home page for mental health support for resources to help the user learn how to support someone struggling with their mental health.
